libxmlccwrap (0.0.7) unstable; urgency=low

  * removed the contructor that loads a xml file
  * renamed getReadErrorString to getErrorString
  * added libxslt as a dependency - now it's also a wrapper around the
    most used xslt function: generate html files with scripts
  * added method .xslt(xsltfilename, outputfilename, parameter) to class
    XMLTree

 -- Juergen Rinas <jrinas@gmx.de>  Tue, 29 Apr 2003 21:21:24 +0200

libxmlccwrap (0.0.6) unstable; urgency=low

  * added some error handling capabilities to the wrapper: read error
    messages from libxml2 will be collected and stored in a string
    variable.
    This variable can be accessed with getReadErrorString(). 

 -- Juergen Rinas <jrinas@gmx.de>  Sat, 26 Apr 2003 20:58:26 +0200

